<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8391938>
    dc:description "FIGURE 14. Eastern Brazil, showing the distribution of the two robust species of Titanoleptes gen. nov., which are allopatrid, distributed in opposite margins of the Doce river." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8391938/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8391942>
    dc:description "FIGURE 16. Titanoleptes calcar (Roewer, 1913), (MNRJ 17818) from Sooretama: a. Male, habitus, dorsal view; b. Same, detail of dorsal scutum; c. Male, coxae I–IV, stigmatic area and free sternites, ventral view; d. Male, body, sinistrolateral view; e. Same, frontal view; f. Same, posterior view; g. Female, dorsal scutum, dorsal view; h. Same, sinistrolateral view. Scale bars = 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8391942/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8391946>
    dc:description "FIGURE 18. Titanoleptes calcar (MNRJ 17850), male genitalia: a. Penis, distal part, dorsal view; b. Same, dextrolateral view; c. Same, ventral view; d. Same, ventro-apical view; e. Glans, ventro-apical view. Scale bars = 100 μm (a, b, c), 50 μm (d), 20 μm (e)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8391946/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

